uare matrix</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is called <b>invert=
ible</b> if there exists an <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">n</span>-by-<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ita=
lic;">n</span> square matrix <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>B</b></span> such t=
hat<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"m=
we-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math=
 display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"=
{\displaystyle \mathbf {AB} =3D\mathbf {BA} =3D\mathbf {I} _{n},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
