<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Gaussian_elimination">Gauss=
ian elimination</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DInvertible_matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Gaussian elimination"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaussian_elimination" title=3D"=
Gaussian elimination">Gaussian elimination</a> is a useful and easy way to =
compute the inverse of a matrix. To compute a matrix inverse using this met=
hod, an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Augmented_matrix" title=3D=
"Augmented matrix">augmented matrix</a> is first created with the left side=
 being the matrix to invert and the right side being the <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Identity_matrix" title=3D"Identity matrix">identity =
matrix</a>. Then, Gaussian elimination is used to convert the left side int=
o the identity matrix, which causes the right side to become the inverse of=
 the input matrix.
</p><p>For example, take the following matrix: <span class=3D"mwe-math-elem=
ent mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math=
-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"htt=
p://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbf {A} =3D{=
\begin{pmatrix}-1&amp;{\tfrac {3}{2}}\\1&amp;-1\end{pmatrix}}}">
  <semantics>
