div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Singularity">Singularity</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInvertible_mat=
rix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Singularity"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>Over a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_(mathematics)" tit=
le=3D"Field (mathematics)">field</a>, a square matrix that is <i>not</i> in=
vertible is called <b>singular</b> or <b>degenerate</b>. A square matrix wi=
th entries in a field is singular <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
If_and_only_if" title=3D"If and only if">if and only if</a> its <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Determinant" title=3D"Determinant">determinan=
t</a> is zero.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Invertible_matrix_theorem">=
Invertible matrix theorem</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DInvertible_matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=
=3D"Edit section: Invertible matrix theorem"><span>edit</span></a><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Let <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> be a square <span class=3D"t=
exhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>-by-<span class=3D"texhtm=
l mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> matrix over a <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_(mathematics)" title=3D"Field (mathematics)=
">field</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K</sp=
an> (e.g., the field <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"mwe-mat=
h-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mw=
e-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.o=
rg/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbb {R} }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"double-struck">R</mi>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbb {R} }=
</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/786849c765da7a84dbc3cce43e96aad58a5868dc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.678ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ma=
thbb {R} }"></span>=E2=81=A0</span> of real numbers). The following stateme=
nts are equivalent, i.e., they are either all true or all false for any giv=
en matrix:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invertible_matrix#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is invertible, i.e. it has =
an inverse under matrix multiplication, i.e., there exists a <span class=3D=
"texhtml"><b>B</b></span> such that <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>AB</b> =3D <=
b>I</b><sub><i>n</i></sub> =3D <b>BA</b></span>. (In that statement, "inver=
tible" can equivalently be replaced with "left-invertible" or "right-invert=
ible" in which one-sided inverses are considered.)</li>
<li>The linear transformation mapping <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>x</b></spa=
n> to <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>Ax</b></span> is invertible, i.e., it has =
an inverse under function composition. (There, again, "invertible" can equi=
valently be replaced with either "left-invertible" or "right-invertible".)<=
/li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transpose" title=3D"Transp=
ose">transpose</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b><sup>T</sup></span> is a=
n invertible matrix.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Row_equivalence" title=3D"Row equivalence">row-equivalent</a> =
to the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>-b=
y-<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Identity_matrix" title=3D"Identity matri=
x">identity matrix</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>I</b><sub><i>n</i></sub><=
/span>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Row_equivalence" title=3D"Row equivalence">column-equivalent</=
a> to the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span=
>-by-<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> ide=
ntity matrix <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>I</b><sub><i>n</i></sub></span>.</l=
i>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> has <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Pivot_position" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Pivot position">pivot =
positions</a>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> has full <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Rank_(linear_algebra)" title=3D"Rank (linear algebra)">r=
ank</a>: <span class=3D"texhtml">rank <b>A</b> =3D <i>n</i></span>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> has a trivial <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kernel_(linear_algebra)" title=3D"Kernel (linear al=
gebra)">kernel</a>: <span class=3D"texhtml">ker(<b>A</b>) =3D {<b>0</b>}.</=
span></li>
<li>The linear transformation mapping <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>x</b></spa=
n> to <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>Ax</b></span> is bijective; that is, the e=
quation <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>Ax</b> =3D <b>b</b></span> has exactly o=
ne solution for each <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>b</b></span> in <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K<sup>n</sup></span>. (There=
, "bijective" can equivalently be replaced with "<a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Injective" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Injective">injecti=
ve</a>" or "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surjective" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Surjective">surjective</a>".)</li>
<li>The columns of <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> form a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basis_of_a_vector_space" class=3D"mw-redi=
rect" title=3D"Basis of a vector space">basis</a> of <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K<sup>n</sup></span>. (In this statemen=
t, "basis" can equivalently be replaced with either "linearly independent s=
et" or "spanning set")</li>
<li>The rows of <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> form a basis of <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K<sup>n</sup></span>=
. (Similarly, here, "basis" can equivalently be replaced with either "linea=
rly independent set" or "spanning set")</li>
<li>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Determinant" title=3D"Dete=
rminant">determinant</a> of <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is nonz=
ero: <span class=3D"texhtml">det <b>A</b> =E2=89=A0 0</span>. In general, a=
 square matrix over a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commutative_=
ring" title=3D"Commutative ring">commutative ring</a> is invertible if and =
only if its determinant is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit_=
(ring_theory)" title=3D"Unit (ring theory)">unit</a> (i.e. multiplicatively=
 invertible element) of that ring.</li>
<li>The number 0 is not an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eigenva=
lue" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Eigenvalue">eigenvalue</a> of <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span>. (More generally, a number <span class=3D"mw=
e-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inli=
ne mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www=
.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \lambda }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CE=BB<!-- =CE=BB --></mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lambda }</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b43d0ea3c9c025af1be9128e62a18fa74bedda2a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.355ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \la=
mbda }"></span> is an eigenvalue of <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span>=
 if the matrix <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><sp=
an class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: =
none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\disp=
laystyle \mathbf {A} -\lambda \mathbf {I} }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"bold">A</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>=CE=BB<!-- =CE=BB --></mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"bold">I</mi>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {A} -=
\lambda \mathbf {I} }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/29a7c87b40de792974d3929d9d1f470e0671caa4" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.505ex; width:7.229ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ma=
thbf {A} -\lambda \mathbf {I} }"></span> is singular, where <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><b>I</b></span> is the identity matrix.)</li>
<li>The matrix <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> can be expressed as =
a finite product of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elementary_mat=
rix" title=3D"Elementary matrix">elementary matrices</a>.</li></ul>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Other_properties">Other pro=
perties</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInve=
rtible_matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D20" title=3D"Edit section: Ot=
her properties"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<p>Furthermore, the following properties hold for an invertible matrix <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span>:
